title: Rocket League is getting a line of toy cars
text:
A limited number will come with an in-game rocket trail and wheel design. Shares 
Rocket League developer Psyonix has joined up with Zag Toys to release a series of 12 miniature toy cars from the game—or, to use the exact nomenclature: 'Original Minis™ Pull-Back Racers'. Snappy! 
The first of the models will be Octane, Dominus, Masamune, Hotshot, Grog, X-Devil, Merc, and Backfire, and they'll all be cased in a rocket ball—which is actually a regular ball that Rocket League cars hit, not a ball with rockets. 
A limited number of special edition cars will also include an in-game rocket trailer and wheel design.
